    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: `uv cache stats` subcommand\n\n### What I found\n\n- **`uv cache size`** lives in `crates/uv/src/commands/cache_size.rs` and uses `diskus::DiskUsage` to measure the whole cache root in one shot.\n- **`CacheBucket`** is a public enum in `crates/uv-cache/src/lib.rs` with 11 variants (`Wheels`, `SourceDistributions`, `FlatIndex`, `Git`, `Interpreter`, `Simple`, `Archive`, `Builds`, `Environments`, `Python`, `Binaries`). `CacheBucket::iter()` returns all except `Python` — I'll include `Python` explicitly since Python downloads can be large.\n- `cache.bucket(bucket)` returns each bucket's `PathBuf`. Per-bucket sizes are measured by calling `DiskUsage::new(vec![bucket_path]).count_ignoring_errors()`, the same pattern as `cache_size`.\n- `human_readable_bytes()` is already in `uv-console` and re-exported through `crate::commands`.\n- The preview feature system uses a bitflag enum; next available bit is `1 << 28`.\n\n### 8 changes across 8 files\n\n1. **`crates/uv-preview/src/lib.rs`** — Add `CacheStats = 1 << 28` variant + `\"cache-stats\"` string in `as_str()` and `FromStr`\n2. **`crates/uv-cli/src/lib.rs`** — Add `Stats(StatsArgs)` to `CacheCommand` enum + new `StatsArgs { human: bool }` struct\n3. **`crates/uv/src/commands/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — Core implementation: iterate all buckets, measure each with `DiskUsage`, print aligned table, sum a total\n4. **`crates/uv/src/commands/mod.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;` + `pub(crate) use cache_stats::cache_stats;`\n5. **`crates/uv/src/lib.rs`** — Dispatch `CacheCommand::Stats(args)` → `commands::cache_stats(...)`\n6. **`crates/uv-test/src/lib.rs`** — Add `cache_stats()` command helper + `with_filtered_cache_stats()` filter\n7. **`crates/uv/tests/it/cache_stats.rs`** *(new)* — Integration tests for empty cache, raw bytes, and `--human`\n8. **`crates/uv/tests/it/main.rs`** — Add `mod cache_stats;`",
